            "correctAnswer": [
                "A"
            ],
            "marks": 1,
            "negativeMarks": 0.25,
            "answerExplanation": {
                "correctExplanation": "Both statements are true and R correctly explains A. Transpiration from leaves creates a negative pressure (suction) that pulls water up the xylem from the roots — this is called the transpiration pull, the major driving force for ascent of sap in tall plants."
